June 4 (Reuters) -  U.S. stocks were largely flat on Wednesday as mixed reads on the economy gave the market little direction and traders were reluctant to buy with indexes near record levels. The Dow Jones industrial average <.DJI> was up 0.04 percent at 16,729.77 and the S&P 500 <.SPX> was up 0.15 percent at 1,927.04. [.N]

